{"id":"8282","name":"LSWeather","tagline":"LSWeather is a Shortcut that runs a Scriptable script to modify your lock screen wallpaper","icon":"ios15 c2071128575 g59845","latest":"30364","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>LSWeather</p>\n<p>A shortcut that runs a Scriptable script to modify your lock screen wallpaper. There are many different layouts to chose from or you can create your own layout.\nYou can find the script <a href=\"https://github.com/ajatkj/scriptable\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Shortcut Configuration-\n1. Set the dictionary key value <code>layout</code> to one of the predefined values <code>'welcome'</code>, <code>'minimalWeather'</code>, <code>'feelMotivated'</code>, <code>'minimalCalendar'</code>, <code>'showMyWork'</code> and <code>'maximalWeather'</code>.\n1. Set the dictionary key value <code>apiKey</code> to your openWeather API key.\n   - Note: if <code>layout</code> and <code>apiKey</code> are not passed from Shortcuts app, it should be defined in the LSWeather script.\n1. You can use either Photos Album or iCloud Folder to pick wallpapers for this script. To change that, look for the dictionary with <code>Photos</code> and <code>iCloud</code> boolean values and set either of them to <code>true</code>. Default is Photos.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>2.1.2 - Oct. 30, 2021, 4:13 p.m.</strong></p><p>- Fixed issues to make it work on iOS 15 (tested on iOS 15.1)</p>"}